This paper is about Scene Graph Generation (SGG), which is a subfield of computer vision that deals with understanding the visual content of images. The paper proposes a new method for SGG that is computationally efficient and can be trained without bounding box annotations. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also introduces a new formulation for SGG called Visual Semantic Parsing, which involves disentangling entity and predicate prediction. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and understanding. 

The proposed method involves a novel three-stage message propagation network and a role-driven attention mechanism, which are both based on deep learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the Visual Genome dataset, which is a large-scale image understanding dataset. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Therefore, the five likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely, are: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM.
